The paper discusses the limitations of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and relational networks (RNs) in learning visual relations, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of feedback mechanisms such as working memory and attention, which are key components of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses controlled experiments to demonstrate the limitations of these networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses visual question answering (VQA) problems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (cs.CL).
